page.title: 10 HIGHBATTS NATURE RESERVE
page.content: The nature reserve at Highbatts is not open to the public. It is privately owened. Mr Colin Slater runs the reserve voluntarily. He has identified 250 different species of moths and 18 different species of butterflies. The rarest bird he has seen there is the Little Egret from Southern France. The rarest bird that has nested is a Lesser Spotted Wood Pecker. His favourite bird he has seen is an Osprey. He has seen four different owls there the Barn Owl, Long Eared Owl and the Tawny Owl and Little Owls have nested there. In the river near the reserve he has seen a pike. Sometimes he puts traps up and in the traps he has caught a commen shrew, pygmy shrew, water shrew, water vole, bank vole,field mouse and a wood mouse.He has never seen a snake but has seen a common lizard.
